news.title: Lucknow development body holds lottery for Anant Nagar Yojana housing scheme
news.para: The lottery for the first phase, comprising 334 plots, was conducted at the Mercury Hall of Indira Gandhi Pratishthan. A total of 13,031 applicants registered online for this phase. The draw is scheduled to continue over the next four days.

news.title: Odisha government notifies second amendment rules for urban development regulations
news.para: According to experts, the new amendment is expected to resolve the long-standing issue of part plot registrations, which were at a standstill for quite a long time due to several litigations and other issues.

news.title: About 10,000 flats in Mahim to be ready in three years: Dharavi project CEO
news.para: The 47.5-acre railway land is part of Dharavi notified area. DRP has physical possession of 28 acres, on which construction for railway quarters is also underway.

news.title: Kochi Metro to lease land near Kaloor station for commercial development
news.para: KMRL issued a tender for commercial lease of 45 cents land adjacent to the metro station. The tender notice stated that KMRL wished to lease out its land to investors or developers who can develop the land parcel.

news.title: Greater Noida: GNIDA wants waste pickup fee, RWAs say paid already
news.para: In a meeting held by GNIDA's health department with representatives from RWAs on Monday, the authority informed residents about the proposed monthly charges for garbage collection.

news.title: NGT ban on sand mining in Jharkhand may affect availability
news.para: An official in the mining and geology department said a letter related to the ban on sand mining from June 10 to October 15 was sent on Monday to all deputy commissioners, who in return have notified it locally.

news.title: Flouting of fire norms rampant across Delhi
news.para: High-rise residential buildings present a recurring pattern. At the time of application for the mandatory dire no-objection certificate (NOC), such buildings maintain proper fire-fighting systems and comply with safety regulations.

news.title: Bihar cabinet approves housing scheme for four lakh women employees
news.para: Following the cabinet meeting, cabinet secretariat department additional chief Secretary S Siddharth said the govt's decision to provide housing would benefit women working in the state secretariat, divisional, district, sub-divisional and block offices, as well as school teachers in both urban and rural areas.

news.title: Government tries to auction flats to recover dues of Newtech Promoters, gets no takers
news.para: The auction was conducted last week by Sadar tehsil as part of recovery proceedings after the builder defaulted on payments worth Rs 5.7 crore. The flats were part of the La Galaxia project in Greater Noida.

news.title: Uncertainty over strategy of JPVL lenders clouds Jaypee Associates' debt resolution
news.para: JPVL - a listed associate of JAL with a market capitalisation of over ₹12,000 crore - is the most valuable asset in JAL's portfolio that also includes real estate, cement and fertiliser plants.

news.title: Raymond Realty to list in early July: Chairman
news.para: "The exact date (for the listing) is not confirmed yet, but it should be early July," Gautam Singhania, chairman and managing director of the group, said in an interview, without elaborating.

news.title: Blackstone gets CCI nod to acquire stake in Kolte-Patil Developers
news.para: Blackstone has secured CCI approval for a ₹1,167 crore investment in Kolte-Patil Developers through preferential allotment and secondary share purchase. This deal involves Blackstone acquiring a 40% stake, potentially rising to 66% after an open offer.

news.title: UK's Bellway raises full-year volume forecast to 8,600-8,700 homes
news.para: Home sales in Britain picked up recently ahead of the April 1 expiry of temporary tax incentives for affordable and first-time buyers, supported by gradual interest rate cuts.

news.title: Chandigarh civic body commissioner, DC discuss collector rate for Manimajra housing
news.para: Sources said both the senior officers had a detailed discussion on the matter, and the DC's office will soon send its reply over the collector's rate through an official letter to MC, so that it can proceed with its housing project.

news.title: Chandigarh gears up for urban land survey under NAKSHA
news.para: The meeting focused on accelerating the preparatory activities crucial to the commencement of the urban land survey under the NAKSHA initiative, which forms a critical component of the Digital India Land Records Modernisation Programme (DILRMP).

news.title: The Wealth Company launches ₹2,000 crore Bharat Bhoomi Fund to invest in real estate
news.para: The fund will focus on data centers, warehousing, hospitality, and renewable parks. fund will also focus on infrastructure-led corridors and plotted developments.

news.title: PG owners across Bengaluru raise alarm over hike in water & sewerage charges by BWSSB
news.para: The PG Association, which represents over 250 owners, submitted a petition to Deputy Chief Minister DK Shivakumar on May 16, 2025, urging the state government to either roll back or revise the recently implemented tariffs.

news.title: JM Financial gets 1.42 lakh sq ft office space in Mumbai through CIRP resolution
news.para: The acquisition is part of a court-mediated corporate insolvency resolution process (CIRP) connected to takeover of a stalled project formerly promoted by Ariisto Realty.

news.title: Mumbai NCLT allows 90-day extension of insolvency resolution for Lavasa Corp
news.para: The planned city project is undergoing a fresh CIRP after the NCLT, in September 2024, directed that the entire process be restarted, following the successful bidder's failure to implement the approved resolution plan within the specified time frame.

news.title: Study to map gaps in mass transit system plan as new Gurugram metro corridor taking shape
news.para: HMRTC has floated a tender for a study, which will be undertaken by a consultant agency expected to be onboarded shortly, with completion targeted within four months.
